SIMPLE: pedarian
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pedarian
<hw>Pe*da"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pedarius</ets>, fr. <ets>pedarius</ets> belonging to the foot, fr.
<ets>pes</ets>, <ets>pedis</ets>, foot.]</ety> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld>
<def>One of a class eligible to the office of senator, but not yet
chosen, who could sit and speak in the senate, but could not vote; -- so
called because he might indicate his opinion by walking over to the side
of the party he favored when a vote was taken.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pedary</ent>⟦br⟧
